statements: SELECT * FROM VolunteerEngagementData WHERE volunteer_id = 1;
SELECT volunteer_name, project_name, hours_volunteered FROM VolunteerEngagementData WHERE engagement_date >= '2022-01-01' ORDER BY engagement_date DESC;
SELECT volunteer_id, volunteer_name, volunteer_role FROM VolunteerEngagementData WHERE project_name = 'Community Cleanup' LIMIT 10;
SELECT * FROM VolunteerEngagementData WHERE hours_volunteered > 5.0 AND volunteer_role = 'Supervisor' ORDER BY hours_volunteered ASC;
SELECT project_name, SUM(hours_volunteered) AS total_hours_volunteered FROM VolunteerEngagementData GROUP BY project_name HAVING total_hours_volunteered > 20.0 ORDER BY total_hours_volunteered DESC;
SELECT * FROM VolunteerEngagementData ORDER BY engagement_date DESC, hours_volunteered ASC
SELECT volunteer_name, SUM(hours_volunteered) AS total_hours FROM VolunteerEngagementData GROUP BY volunteer_name HAVING total_hours > 10
SELECT volunteer_name, project_name, engagement_date FROM VolunteerEngagementData WHERE engagement_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-06-30' ORDER BY volunteer_name
SELECT DISTINCT project_name FROM VolunteerEngagementData
SELECT volunteer_name, COUNT(DISTINCT project_name) AS unique_projects FROM VolunteerEngagementData GROUP BY volunteer_name HAVING unique_projects >= 2

SELECT Volunteer.volunteer_name, Activity.activity_name FROM Volunteer INNER JOIN Participation ON Volunteer.volunteer_id = Participation.volunteer_id INNER JOIN Activity ON Participation.activity_id = Activity.activity_id;
SELECT Feedback.feedback_text, Feedback.feedback_date FROM Feedback INNER JOIN Participation ON Feedback.participation_id = Participation.participation_id WHERE Participation.activity_id = 1;

SELECT skill_name, COUNT(volunteer_id) FROM skills JOIN volunteer_skills ON skills.skill_id = volunteer_skills.skill_id GROUP BY skill_name;
SELECT activity_name, date FROM activities ORDER BY date DESC LIMIT 3;

SELECT * FROM volunteers;
SELECT volunteer_id, first_name, last_name, email FROM volunteers WHERE join_date > '2021-01-01';

SELECT v.first_name, v.last_name, a.activity_name FROM volunteers v JOIN volunteer_hours vh ON v.volunteer_id = vh.volunteer_id JOIN activities a ON a.activity_id = vh.activity_id WHERE vh.hours > 10;
SELECT v.first_name, s.skill_name FROM volunteers v JOIN volunteer_skills vs ON v.volunteer_id = vs.volunteer_id JOIN skills s ON s.skill_id = vs.skill_id;

SELECT v.first_name, v.last_name, SUM(vh.hours) AS total_hours FROM volunteers v JOIN volunteer_hours vh ON v.volunteer_id = vh.volunteer_id GROUP BY v.first_name, v.last_name ORDER BY total_hours DESC;
